eaving children still in diapers","body":"Samuel Talcott died May 26, 1813 at age 56 — two years after his father Deacon Benjamin. At his death his oldest son was 20 and his youngest son James had just been born. He left an estate valued at $5,215, including a home lot and buildings worth $1,650."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Named replacement children after two he lost","body":"Their first daughter Sarah died at ten days old in March 1796, and the next daughter, born fourteen months later, was given the same name. The pattern repeated with James Tudor — when the first one died at three months in 1811, they gave the name to their final son, born two years later in 1813."}],"sources":[{"label":"Tankerhoosen Valley History","url":"https://www.tankerhoosen.info/history/talcott_vernon.htm"}],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"quotes":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"statues":[],"bio":{"title":"Deacon","first_name":"Samuel","last_name":"Talcott","married_names":[],"display_name":"Deacon Samuel Talcott"},"military_service":[],"slug":"samuel-talcott-1757"},"I00259":{"id":"I00259","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":true,"gender":"female","classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":true,"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_paths_to_thomas":0,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1765,"month":12,"day":20},"death":{"year":1823,"month":2,"day":16,"city":"Vernon","county":"Tolland","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM124","plot_notes":"Southwest Cemetery, Vernon CT."},"parents":{"father_research_notes":"James Smith of Cromwell CT","mother_research_notes":"Mary Tudor Smith of Cromwell CT"},"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id